


@{ViewBag.Title = "London Underground services on Monday";}
        
        

<div class="r">
    <div class="headline-container plain">
        <h1>London Underground services on Monday</h1>
        <div class="content-page-press-release">
        24 July 2005
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        From start of service on Monday 25 July 2005, Aldgate station will re-open. The remaining Metropolitan line suspension, due to 7 July incidents, will be lifted and a full service will re-commence. Trains will travel through to Aldgate rather than terminating at Moorgate.<BR>        <BR>            <BR>                        <BR>            <BR>            <BR>            <BR>            It is expected that services will be operating as follows:<BR>Bakerloo - normal service<BR>Central - normal service
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<p><strong>Circle</strong> - suspended (due to 7 July incidents)</p>
<p><strong>District</strong> - suspended between Edgware Road and High Street Kensington (due to 7 July incidents)</p>
<p><strong>East London </strong>- normal service</p>
<p><strong>Hammersmith &amp; City </strong>- shuttle service every 15 minutes between Hammersmith and Paddington in both directions. During morning and evening peak there will be a limited service between Baker Street and Whitechapel in both directions. </p>
<p><strong>Jubilee</strong> - normal service</p>
<p><strong>Metropolitan</strong> - normal service</p>
<p><strong>Northern</strong> - normal service</p>
<p><strong>Piccadilly </strong>-suspended between Hyde Park Corner and Arnos Grove and between Rayners Lane and Uxbridge (due to 7 July incidents).</p>
<p>Until further notice, a special bus service calls at Arnos Grove and Finchley Central to provide a connection with the Northern line. A second special bus service calls at Arnos Grove, Bounds Green, Wood Green, Turnpike Lane and Seven Sisters to connect with Victoria line services.</p>
<p>Additional bus services are operating on route 91 between Holloway Road and Euston via Caledonian Road and King's Cross St Pancras.</p>
<p><strong>Victoria line</strong> - normal service</p>
<p><strong>Waterloo &amp; City</strong> - normal service</p>
<p>For 24-hour information on all London travel, please call: 020-7222 1234 or visit TfL's website: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk">www.tfl.gov.uk</a></p>

     

        
        
        
